An Act relative to certain employees of the MBTA advisory board.
Whereas, The deferred operation of this act would tend to defeat its purpose, which is to
establish forthwith retirement benefits to persons whose regular compensation is paid by
Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority advisory board, therefore it is hereby declared to be
an emergency law, necessary for the immediate preservation of the public convenience.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. The definition of “Employee” in section 1 of chapter 32 of the General
2 Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following
3 sentence:- ''Employee'', as applied to persons whose regular compensation is paid by the advisory
4 board to the Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority established in chapter 161A, shall
5 mean any person who is engaged in duties which require that the person’s time be devoted to the
6 service of said advisory board in each year during the ordinary working hours of regular and
7 permanent employees.
